card.name: Blue-Eyes White Dragon
card.description: This legendary dragon is a powerful engine of destruction. Virtually invincible, very few have faced this awesome creature and lived to tell the tale.

card.name: Hitotsu-Me Giant
card.description: A one-eyed behemoth with thick, powerful arms made for delivering punishing blows.

card.name: Ryu-Kishin
card.description: A very elusive creature that looks like a harmless statue until it attacks.

card.name: The Wicked Worm Beast
card.description: This face-up card on the field is returned to the owner's hand during the End Phase of your turn.

card.name: Battle Ox
card.description: A monster with tremendous power, it destroys enemies with a swing of its axe.

card.name: Koumori Dragon
card.description: A vicious, fire-breathing dragon whose wicked flame corrupts the souls of its victims.

card.name: Judge Man
card.description: This club-wielding warrior battles to the end and will never surrender.

card.name: Rogue Doll
card.description: A deadly doll gifted with mystical power, it is particularly powerful when attacking against dark forces.

card.name: Kojikocy
card.description: A man-hunter with powerful arms that can crush boulders.

card.name: Uraby
card.description: Fast on its feet, this dinosaur rips enemies to shreds with its sharp claws.

card.name: Gyakutenno Megami
card.description: This fairy uses her mystical power to protect the weak and provide spiritual support.

card.name: Mystic Horseman
card.description: Half man and half horse, this monster is known for its extreme speed.

card.name: Terra the Terrible
card.description: Known as a swamp dweller, this creature is a minion of the dark forces.

card.name: Dark Titan of Terror
card.description: A fiend said to dwell in the world of dreams, it attacks enemies in their sleep.

card.name: Dark Assailant
card.description: Armed with the Psycho Sword, this sinister assassin rules the bad land.

card.name: Master & Expert
card.description: A deadly duo consisting of a beast master and its loyal servant.

card.name: Unknown Warrior of Fiend
card.description: The speed of this warrior creates an intense vacuum that can slice through a monster's hide.

card.name: Mystic Clown
card.description: Nothing can stop the mad attack of this powerful creature.

card.name: Ogre of the Black Shadow
card.description: An ogre possessed by the powers of the dark. Few can withstand its rapid charge.

card.name: Dark Energy
card.description: A Fiend-Type monster equipped with this card increases its ATK and DEF by 300 points.

card.name: Invigoration
card.description: An EARTH monster equipped with this card increases its ATK by 400 points and decreases its DEF by 200 points.

card.name: Dark Hole
card.description: Destroy all monsters on the field.

card.name: Ookazi
card.description: Inflict 800 points of damage to your opponent's Life Points.

card.name: Ryu-Kishin Powered
card.description: A gargoyle enhanced by the powers of darkness. Very sharp talons make it a worthy opponent.

card.name: Swordstalker
card.description: A monster formed by the vengeful souls of those who passed away in battle.

card.name: La Jinn the Mystical Genie of the Lamp
card.description: A genie of the lamp that is at the beck and call of its master.

card.name: Rude Kaiser
card.description: With an axe in each hand, this monster delivers heavy damage.

card.name: Destroyer Golem
card.description: A golem with a massive right hand for crushing its victims.

card.name: Skull Red Bird
card.description: This monster swoops down and attacks with a rain of knives stored in its wings.

card.name: D. Human
card.description: Gifted with the power of dragons, this warrior wields a sword created from a dragon's fang.

card.name: Pale Beast
card.description: With skin tinged a bluish-white, this strange creature is a fearsome sight to behold.

card.name: Fissure
card.description: Destroy the 1 face-up monster your opponent controls that has the lowest ATK (your choice, if tied).

card.name: Trap Hole
card.description: When your opponent Normal or Flip Summons 1 monster with 1000 or more ATK: Target that monster; destroy that target.

card.name: Two-Pronged Attack
card.description: Select and destroy 2 of your monsters and 1 of your opponent's monsters.

card.name: De-Spell
card.description: Target 1 face-up Spell, or 1 Set Spell/Trap, on the field; destroy that target if it is a Spell. (If the target is Set, reveal it.)

card.name: Monster Reborn
card.description: Target 1 monster in either GY; Special Summon it.

card.name: The Inexperienced Spy
card.description: Select and see 1 card in your opponent's hand.

card.name: Reinforcements
card.description: Target 1 face-up monster on the field; it gains 500 ATK until the end of this turn.

card.name: Ancient Telescope
card.description: See the top 5 cards of your opponent's Deck. Return the cards to the Deck in the same order.

card.name: Just Desserts
card.description: Inflict 500 damage to your opponent for each monster they control.

card.name: Lord of D.
card.description: Neither player can target Dragon monsters on the field with card effects.

card.name: The Flute of Summoning Dragon
card.description: Special Summon up to 2 Dragon monsters from your hand. "Lord of D." must be on the field to activate and to resolve this effect.

card.name: Mysterious Puppeteer
card.description: Each time you or your opponent Normal Summons or Flip Summons a monster, increase your Life Points by 500 points.

card.name: Trap Master
card.description: FLIP: Select 1 Trap Card on the field and destroy it. If the selected card is Set, pick up and see the card. If it is a Trap Card, it is destroyed. If it is a Spell Card, return it to its original position.

card.name: Sogen
card.description: All Warrior and Beast-Warrior monsters on the field gain 200 ATK/DEF.

card.name: Hane-Hane
card.description: FLIP: Select 1 monster on the field and return it to its owner's hand.

card.name: Reverse Trap
card.description: Until the End Phase, all effects that add or subtract ATK or DEF are reversed. (Additions now subtract, and subtractions now add, instead. Multiplications and divisions, including halving/doubling, are not affected.)

card.name: Remove Trap
card.description: Select 1 face-up Trap Card on the field and destroy it.

card.name: Castle Walls
card.description: Increase a selected monster's DEF by 500 points during the turn this card is activated.

card.name: Ultimate Offering
card.description: During your Main Phase or your opponent's Battle Phase: You can pay 500 Life Points; immediately after this effect resolves, Normal Summon/Set 1 monster.
